An ANC councillor in Mpumalanga has been arrested for allegedly selling fraudulent permits to informal business owners. JOHANNESBURG - The ANC in Mpumalanga has suspended one of its councillors from the party. He will now face an internal disciplinary process and criminal charges. Musawenkosi Masina was arrested for selling fraudulent permits to informal business owners. After being released on a warning, he was bust again, doing the same thing. READ: SA lockdown: Informal traders confused about regulations He's now in police custody. ANC's Lindiwe Ntshalintshali says the party is disappointed by Masina's conduct. She says Masina has been suspended from all party activities until a disciplinary hearing in his conduct has been concluded. "We have a resolution, we have our policies and we have the constitution on how members and deployees of the ANC should behave when they are in government," she said. The lockdown has forced many informal traders in the townships to close their businesses and only those with permits are allowed to do business. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.